    "4 Extensions 4.1 Fixed Factors and the Return of Scarcity If labor is dethroned as the most important factor of production, it becomes useful to disentangle the remaining factors, which have traditionally been lumped together into capital in the economic models of the Industrial Age.",
    "Let us distinguish between factors that are in xed supply and factors that are reproducible and can therefore be accumulated.",
    "We continue to call all reproducible factors capital, including compute, robots, power plants, and factories.",
    "By 6 It is dicult to predict which scarce factors will matter the most in an AGI-powered future in the short term, it is likely that microchips and the semiconductor fabrication equipment (fabs) used for producing these chips will be bottlenecks, but these are clearly reproducible.",
    "By contrast, the raw materials going into the production of chips, for example certain rare earth minerals, are irreproducible."
